originalText.text: This precinct is a complete joke. Super bad attitudes, unwilling to help. Don't understand basic procedures, laws, or jurisdiction. Had to request to speak to a supervisor to simply file a simple report for lost license plates. If you can, save yourself the trip and go to a more competent precinct/staff.

originalText.text: I had an accident on the RFK Bridge on August 31, 2016. It involved multiple cars. The police from the 25th Precinct in East Harlem arrived in record time. They were unbelievable and made an unbearable situation, bearable. A few days later, I called the precinct to ask about the status of my accident report. The phone was answered quickly and the officer was courteous and very helpful. On September 9th, I went to the precinct to pick up my report. The person in front of me was very "needy." The officer handled him with the utmost respect. I was in and out  in 10 minutes. I know this is a long post but these police officers deserve to know that their service is recognized and appreciated. God Bless Them and Keep Them Safe.

originalText.text:
How unfortunate I am living where this precinct presides.  I've lived in New York City for over 15 years, from Greenwich Village, to the Upper West Side, and, for the past 8 years, East Harlem.  Over the past 8 years, this precinct has NEVER responded promptly (mostly never showing up at all), or professionally when they actually do show up.

I feel incredibly unsafe in my neighborhood because I live in an area where the police can not show up and it seems no one cares or does anything about it.  I actually live in a nice apartment which I may now have to give up because I can't feel safe when my police precinct treats us like we're a joke.  Just to give you an idea, I've called about everything from a fight breaking out across the street in the park, to a person passed out on the street, to a petty theft in the building and they have never once shown up or responded.  You'd be lucky to see a police car drive by.  Don't try to flag them.  They'll just look at you (if you're lucky) and drive by.

originalText.text:
The cops, here are disrespectful, so are the EMT's that show up. A domestic incident occurred in my mothers apartment, I went to defend myself- another family member attacked me. Then decided to call the police. The officers that came up, disrespected me to my face, one called me a "Dyke" and an EMT tried to chastise me by talking to me in a nasty tone, telling me that he gets to "choose the hospital YOU go to" he then tried to tell me that I was mentally incompetent because he claimed that I had "another un -diagnosed mental condition" and that I'm not on medication.
I reported the police officers to the Civilian Report Board, and they closed the case. The funny thing about it is that when I called the precinct they had no record of any of the reports that were filed. I guess they were mad that they couldn't arrest me to fill their quota for the month.
